[I] Extract, test and view RAR archives

[T] Unrar is a package to handle files compressed in the RAR format.
[T] Due to strange licensing issues this package can only view, test
[T] and extract files in a given archive, but not pack files.
[T] But since we have far more advanced open-source compression utils
[T] it should be enough to extract the content when you get a RAR
[T] archive.

[U] https://www.rarlab.com

[A] Eugene Roshal <roshal@rarlab.com>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] base/tool
[F] CROSS

[L] Free-to-use
[V] 7.2.6
[P] X -----5---9 162.000

[CV-URL] https://www.rarlab.com/rar_add.htm
[D] f62cf62a4ae4770bfaff3dc0471b9d2bf19bc64f1823f80654cf4299 unrarsrc-7.2.6.tar.gz https://www.rarlab.com/rar/

